[The latest issue of CDC's Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report includes
the original reports on which the above article is based. One of these
describes outbreaks of cryptosporidiosis associated with pools in Ohio and
Nebraska in 2000. The other describes a study carried out in 1999, in which
none of the 293 stools collected from 47 participating pools following
fecal accidents were found to contain cryptosporidium but 13 contained
giardia, another pathogen responsible for prolonged diarrhea and
malabsorption. The reports are available online at:
<http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm5020a3.htm>
and
<http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/mm5020a4.htm> - Mod.SH
